title: Seoraksan
author: Unknown
pages:
Seoraksan is the
highest mountain in the
Taebaek mountain
range in the Gangwon
Province in eastern
South Korea. After
the Hallasan volcano
on Jeju Island and
Jirisan in the south,
Seoraksan is the third
highest mountain in
South, and is
sometimes considered
the backbone of South

Korea. Some notable
locations at
Seoraksan include the
Yukdam and Biryeong
waterfalls, Dinosaur
Ridge, and the
Sinheungsa Buddhist
Temple.
